primary.context: Caller wanted instructions on what to do with a rental agreement
primary.detail: The agent offered to send the link and asked if there was anything else, but never confirmed the link was actually sent.

steps: Caller asked for instructions on rental agreement.
Agent performed account lookup and identity verification (name spelling and state).
Agent identified the specific contract and property.
Agent offered to send a rental agreement link via email and text.
Caller accepted, but agent moved to closing without confirming the send action was successful.

failure.detail: Agent moved to call closing before confirming the rental link was actually sent to the user.

actions.detail: Offered link but never confirmed delivery

insights.summary: The caller wanted to know how to handle a rental agreement. The agent verified the caller and offered to send a link, but ended the call before confirming the link was sent.
insights.verbatim: What do I do with the rental agreement?
insights.coaching: The agent should confirm the link has been sent (e.g., 'I have sent that link now') before asking if there is anything else and ending the call.
